body:
Thanks! My biggest concern was resolved.  I do still have the minor "nit" that the `@expose` annotation (which should, to some extent, serve as documentation of the method's behavior) is now not necessarily consistent with its actual behavior.

Obvs this is not the end of the world, so disregard if you don't want to do this... but if you use the annotation it will keep it correct and it won't require any new code to handle the restricted behavior.

```
    EXPLORE_JSON_METHODS = ['POST']
    if not is_feature_enabled('ENABLE_EXPLORE_JSON_CSRF_PROTECTION'):
      EXPLORE_JSON_METHODS.append('GET')

    @expose('/explore_json/<datasource_type>/<datasource_id>/', methods=EXPLORE_JSON_METHODS)
    @expose('/explore_json/', methods=EXPLORE_JSON_METHODS)
    def explore_json(self, datasource_type=None, datasource_id=None):
        # here we can get rid of the block that checks the setting
```
